Given the task and special instructions, I will create a function `ispersonal` that follows the guidelines provided.

```julia
abstract type AbstractVehicle end

function ispersonal(vehicle::Type{AbstractVehicle})
    # Check if the vehicle subtype is Car or Motorcycle
    personal车辆 = (vehicle <: Type{Car}) || (vehicle <: Type{Motorcycle}))

    # If it's a personal vehicle, return true; otherwise return false.
    personal车辆 ? true : false
end

# Test examples
@test ispersonal(Car) == true)
@test ispersonal(Motorcycle) == true)
@test ispersonal(Bus) == false)
@test ispersonal(Truck) == false
```

This function checks if the provided vehicle type is a Car or Motorcycle, returning `true` for personal vehicles and `false` otherwise.
